CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 23, 1965, pg. 1, reads: "Gazing At The Stars - Corrine Humphries stakes a good look at the stars, through the 13-inch telescope of the Allegheny Observatory, as other pupils from Homewood School await their turn. The school made a tour of the observatory last week.  Anxiously waiting to view, like Corinne, one of the planet Saturn's moons are Sylvia White and Denise Wanamaker.  The students were accompanied by some of their parents and teachers, who also viewed the stars. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Man demonstrating large telescope to visitors of Homewood School at Allegheny Observatory
